\f1\b0\fs22 \cf0 		This Act may be cited as the 
\f2\i Acts Interpretation Act 1901
\f1\i0 .\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 1A  Simplified outline\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf0 		The following is a simplified outline of this Act:\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f2\i \cf0 Overview\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f1\i0 \cf0 This Act is like a dictionary and manual to use when reading and interpreting Commonwealth Acts and instruments made under Commonwealth Acts.\
The definitions and many of the interpretation rules are aimed at making Commonwealth legislation shorter, less complex and more consistent in operation.\
A provision of this Act is subject to a contrary intention in other Commonwealth legislation.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f2\i \cf0 Structure\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f1\i0 \cf0 Part\'a01 provides that this Act applies to all Acts. This Act also applies to legislative instruments, notifiable instruments and other instruments made under an Act (see subsection\'a013(1) of the 
\f2\i Legislation Act 2003
\f1\i0  and subsection\'a046(1) of this Act).\
Part\'a02 contains definitions that apply across all Commonwealth legislation (for example, 
\f3\i\b Australian citizen
\f1\i0\b0 , 
\f3\i\b business day
\f1\i0\b0 , 
\f3\i\b document
\f1\i0\b0  and 
\f3\i\b month
\f1\i0\b0 ).\
Part\'a03 deals with the commencement of Commonwealth Acts. For example, section\'a04 allows certain powers to be exercised (like the making of appointments) between the enactment and commencement of an Act.\
Part\'a04 deals with the amendment, repeal and expiry of Commonwealth legislation. For example, section\'a07 provides that the repeal of an Act does not affect any rights accrued under the Act, or any legal proceedings instituted, before the repeal.\
Part\'a05 contains various rules for interpreting Commonwealth legislation, including:\
\pard\tqr\tx1786\pardeftab720\li2070\fi-936\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	section\'a015A (about interpreting an Act subject to the Constitution); and\
	(b)	section\'a015AA (which provides for interpreting an Act in a way that best achieves the purpose or object of the Act); and\
	(c)	section\'a015AB (about using material that is not part of an Act (like explanatory memorandums and second reading speeches) in interpreting an Act); and\
	(d)	sections\'a019 to 20 (which deal generally with references to Ministers and Departments in Acts, with the effect of machinery of government changes on references to Ministers and Departments and other authorities in Acts and Commonwealth agreements, and with the validity of acts done by Ministers).\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 Part\'a06 deals with the service of documents on persons.\
Part\'a07 contains rules about exercising powers and performing functions and duties under Commonwealth legislation, including:\
\pard\tqr\tx1786\pardeftab720\li2070\fi-936\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	subsection\'a033(3) (which provides that a power to make an instrument includes the power to vary or revoke the instrument); and\
	(b)	section\'a033A (about acting appointments); and\
	(c)	sections\'a034AA, 34AB and 34A (about delegating powers, functions and duties).\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 Part\'a08 deals with the calculation of distance, time and age.\
Part\'a09 deals with the citation of Acts.\
Part\'a010 deals with instruments other than legislative instruments or notifiable instruments. For example, it provides that this Act applies to those instruments and that expressions in those instruments have the same meaning as in the enabling legislation.\
Part\'a011 contains a regulation\uc0\u8209 making power.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

