\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 2C  References to persons\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf0 	(1)	In any Act, expressions used to denote persons generally (such as \'93person\'94, \'93party\'94, \'93someone\'94, \'93anyone\'94, \'93no\uc0\u8209 one\'94, \'93one\'94, \'93another\'94 and \'93whoever\'94), include a body politic or corporate as well as an individual.\
	(2)	Express references in an Act to companies, corporations or bodies corporate do not imply that expressions in that Act, of the kind mentioned in subsection\'a0(1), do not include companies, corporations or bodies corporate.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 2CA  References to spouses\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf0 	(1)	For the purposes of any Act, a person is the 
\f3\i\b spouse
\f1\i0\b0  of another person (whether of the same sex or a different sex) if the person is legally married to the other person.\
	(2)	Subsection\'a0(1) has effect in addition to any provision of an Act that affects the meaning of 
\f3\i\b spouse
\f1\i0\b0  in a provision of that Act.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1985\fi-851\ri1933\sb122\partightenfactor0

\fs18 \cf0 Example:	
\f3\i\b Spouse
\f1\i0\b0  is defined for the purposes of an Act to include a\'a0de\'a0facto\'a0partner and a former spouse. Because of this section, a reference in the Act to a person\'92s spouse covers any person who is legally married to the person, in addition to any person covered by the definition in the Act.\
\pard\tx6677\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 2D  References to de\'a0facto partners\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\tx6677\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf0 		For the purposes of a provision of an Act that is a provision in which de\'a0facto partner has the meaning given by this Act, a person is the 
\f3\i\b de\'a0facto partner 
\f1\i0\b0 of another person (whether of the same sex or a different sex) if:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	the person is in a registered relationship with the other person under section\'a02E; or\
	(b)	the person is in a de\'a0facto relationship with the other person under section\'a02F.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 2E  Registered relationships\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\tx6677\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf0 		For the purposes of paragraph\'a02D(a), a person is in a 
\f3\i\b registered relationship 
\f1\i0\b0 with another person if the relationship between the persons is registered under a prescribed law of a State or Territory as a prescribed kind of relationship.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 2F  De\'a0facto relationships\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf0 	(1)	For the purposes of paragraph\'a02D(b), a person is in a 
\f3\i\b de\'a0facto relationship 
\f1\i0\b0 with another person if the persons:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	are not legally married to each other; and\
	(b)	are not related by family (see subsection\'a0(6)); and\
	(c)	have a relationship as a couple living together on a genuine domestic basis.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\tx6677\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(2)	In determining for the purposes of paragraph\'a0(1)(c) whether 2 persons have a relationship as a couple, all the circumstances of their relationship are to be taken into account, including any or all of the following circumstances:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\tx6677\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	the duration of the relationship;\
	(b)	the nature and extent of their common residence;\
	(c)	whether a sexual relationship exists;\
	(d)	the degree of financial dependence or interdependence, and any arrangements for financial support, between them;\
	(e)	the ownership, use and acquisition of their property;\
	(f)	the degree of mutual commitment to a shared life;\
	(g)	the care and support of children;\
	(h)	the reputation and public aspects of the relationship.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\tx6677\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(3)	No particular finding in relation to any circumstance mentioned in subsection\'a0(2) is necessary in determining whether 2 persons have a relationship as a couple for the purposes of paragraph\'a0(1)(c).\
	(4)	For the purposes of paragraph\'a0(1)(c), the persons are taken to be living together on a genuine domestic basis if the persons are not living together on a genuine domestic basis only because of:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	a temporary absence from each other; or\
	(b)	illness or infirmity of either or both of them.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\tx6677\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(5)	For the purposes of subsection\'a0(1), a de\'a0facto relationship can exist even if one of the persons is legally married to someone else or is in a registered relationship (within the meaning of section\'a02E) with someone else or is in another de\'a0facto relationship.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(6)	For the purposes of paragraph\'a0(1)(b), 2 persons are 
\f3\i\b related by family
\f1\i0\b0  if:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	one is the child (including an adopted child) of the other; or\
	(b)	one is another descendant of the other (even if the relationship between them is traced through an adoptive parent); or\
	(c)	they have a parent in common (who may be an adoptive parent of either or both of them).\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 For this purpose, disregard whether an adoption is declared void or has ceased to have effect.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(7)	For the purposes of subsection\'a0(6), 
\f3\i\b adopted 
\f1\i0\b0 means adopted under the law of any place (whether in or out of Australia) relating to the adoption of children.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 2G  Months\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf0 	(1)	In any Act, 
\f3\i\b month
\f1\i0\b0  means a period:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	starting at the start of any day of one of the calendar months; and\
	(b)	ending:\
\pard\tqr\tx1985\pardeftab720\li2098\fi-2098\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(i)	immediately before the start of the corresponding day of the next calendar month; or\
	(ii)	if there is no such day\'97at the end of the next calendar month.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1985\fi-851\ri1933\sb122\partightenfactor0

\fs18 \cf0 Example 1:	A month starting on 15\'a0December in a year ends immediately before 15\'a0January in the next year.\
Example 2:	A month starting on 31\'a0August in a year ends at the end of September in that year (because September is the calendar month coming after August and does not have 31 days).\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\fs22 \cf0 	(2)	In any Act, a reference to a period of 2 or more months is a reference to a period:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	starting at the start of a day of one of the calendar months (the 
\f3\i\b starting month
\f1\i0\b0 ); and\
	(b)	ending:\
\pard\tqr\tx1985\pardeftab720\li2098\fi-2098\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(i)	immediately before the start of the corresponding day of the calendar month that is that number of calendar months after the starting month; or\
	(ii)	if there is no such day\'97at the end of the calendar month that is that number of calendar months after the starting month.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1985\fi-851\ri1933\sb122\partightenfactor0

\fs18 \cf0 Example 1:	A reference to 6 months starting on 15\'a0December in a year is a reference to a period starting on that day and ending immediately before 15\'a0June in the next year.\
Example 2:	A reference to 6 months starting on 31\'a0October in a year is a reference to a period starting on that day and ending at the end of April in the next year (because April is the calendar month coming sixth after October and does not have 31 days).\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 2H  References to law of the Commonwealth\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf0 		In any Act, a reference to the law of the Commonwealth, or to a law of the Commonwealth, does not include, and is taken never to have included, a reference to a law in force in a Territory so far as the law is so in force because of an Act providing for the acceptance, administration or government of that Territory.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 2J  Documents commencing proceedings\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf0 		A reference in a provision of an Act to any one or more of the following in connection with court proceedings:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	a summons;\
	(b)	an information;\
	(c)	a claim;\
	(d)	a complaint;\
	(e)	a declaration;\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 is taken to include a reference to any document through which proceedings may be instituted in a court.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1985\fi-851\ri1933\sb122\partightenfactor0

\fs18 \cf0 Note:	An example of such a document is a court attendance notice under the 
\f2\i Criminal Procedure Act 1986 
\f1\i0 of New South Wales.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 2K  Rules of court\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf0 	(1)	In any Act, 
\f3\i\b rules of court
\f1\i0\b0 ,
\f3\i\b  
\f1\i0\b0 in relation to any court, means rules made by the authority having for the time being power to make rules or orders regulating the practice and procedure of such court.\
	(2)	The power of the authority to make rules of court includes a power to make rules of court for the purpose of any Act which directs or authorises anything to be done by rules of court.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 2L  References to Australian Standards\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf0 		In any Act, a reference consisting of the words \'93Australian Standard\'94 followed by the letters \'93AS\'94 and a number is a reference to the standard so numbered that is published by, or on behalf of, Standards Australia.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 2M  Sitting day\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf0 	(1)	In any Act, a 
\f3\i\b sitting day
\f1\i0\b0 , in relation to a House of the Parliament, is a day on which the House actually sits.\
	(2)	However, if the House sat without adjourning on a previous day (the 
\f3\i\b earlier sitting day
\f1\i0\b0 ), any period during which the House continues to sit, with or without a suspension, on a later day, until it adjourns, is taken to be part of the earlier sitting day.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1985\fi-851\ri1933\sb122\partightenfactor0

\fs18 \cf0 Example 1:	The Senate begins sitting at 9 am on Thursday and extends (with or without a suspension of the sitting) until it is adjourned at 3 pm on Friday. Thursday is a sitting day for the Senate but Friday is not. This example applies equally to the House of Representatives.\
Example 2:	The House of Representatives begins sitting at 9 am on Wednesday and extends (with or without a suspension of the sitting) until it is adjourned at 1 am on Thursday. The House of Representatives then starts sitting again at 10 am on Thursday and adjourns at 3 pm on Thursday. Both Wednesday and Thursday are sitting days for the House of Representatives. This example applies equally to the Senate.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\fs22 \cf0 	(3)	For the purposes of this section, a House is taken to have adjourned if:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	the Parliament is prorogued; or\
	(b)	that House is dissolved; or\
	(c)	if that House is the House of Representatives\'97that House expires.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 Part\'a03\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\'97\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Commencement of Acts\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri1933\sl-160\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs16 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0   \
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 3  When Acts come into operation\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf0 		If an Act or a provision of an Act is expressed to come into operation on a particular day (whether the expression \'93come into operation\'94 or \'93commence\'94 is used), it comes into operation at the start of the day.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 3A\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
  Commencement of Acts\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 	(1)	This section does not apply to an Act so far as it provides for its commencement.\
	(2)	An Act (other than an Act to alter the Constitution) commences on the 28th day after the day on which that Act receives the Royal Assent.\
	(3)	An Act to alter the Constitution commences on the day on which that Act receives the Royal Assent.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 4  Exercise of powers between enactment and commencement of Act\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f2\i\b0\fs22 \cf0 Application of section\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\i0 \cf0 	(1)	This section applies if an Act is enacted and at a time (the 
\f3\i\b start time
\f1\i0\b0 ) after its enactment the Act will confer power to make an appointment, or to make an instrument of a legislative or administrative character (including rules, regulations or by\uc0\u8209 laws), because:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	the Act will commence at the start time; or\
	(b)	the Act will be amended at the start time by an Act that has been enacted and that commences at that time.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f2\i \cf0 Exercise of power before start time\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\i0 \cf0 	(2)	The power may be exercised before the start time as if the relevant commencement had occurred.\
	(3)	Anything may be done before the start time for the purpose of enabling the exercise of the power, or of bringing the appointment or instrument into effect, as if the relevant commencement had occurred.\
	(4)	The exercise of a power under subsection\'a0(2) does not confer a power or right or impose an obligation on a person before the relevant commencement except so far as is necessary or convenient for the purpose of:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	bringing the appointment or instrument into effect; or\
	(b)	bringing the Act conferring power into operation; or\
	(c)	making the Act conferring power fully effective at or after the start time.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(5)	An appointment, or a provision of an instrument, made under subsection\'a0(2) takes effect at the start time or a later time specified in the appointment or instrument.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f2\i \cf0 One instrument may rely on subsection\'a0(2) and existing power\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\i0 \cf0 	(6)	To avoid doubt, a single instrument may be made before the start time partly under subsection\'a0(2) and partly under a power already conferred by an Act.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f2\i \cf0 Extended application to provisions of an Act\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\i0 \cf0 	(7)	Subsections\'a0(1) to (6) also apply in relation to a provision of an Act in the same way as they apply in relation to an Act.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 6  Evidence of date of assent\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf0 		The date appearing on the copy of an Act printed by the Government Printer, and purporting to be the date on which the Governor\uc0\u8209 General assented thereto, or made known the Sovereign\'92s assent, shall be evidence that such date was the date on which the Governor\u8209 General so assented or made known the Sovereign\'92s assent, and shall be judicially noticed.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 Part\'a04\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\'97\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Amendment, repeal and expiry of Acts\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri1933\sl-160\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs16 \cf0   \
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 7\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
  Effect of repeal or amendment of Act\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f2\i\b0\fs22 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 No revival of other Act or part\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\i0 \cf0 	(1)	The repeal of an Act, or of a part of an Act, that repealed an Act (the 
\f3\i\b old Act
\f1\i0\b0 ) or part (the 
\f3\i\b old part
\f1\i0\b0 ) of an Act does not revive the old Act or old part, unless express provision is made for the revival.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f2\i \cf0 No effect on previous operation of Act or part\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\i0 \cf0 	(2)	If an Act, or an instrument under an Act, repeals or amends an Act (the 
\f3\i\b affected Act
\f1\i0\b0 ) or a part of an Act, then the repeal or amendment does not:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	revive anything not in force or existing at the time at which the repeal or amendment takes effect; or\
	(b)	affect the previous operation of the affected Act or part (including any amendment made by the affected Act or part), or anything duly done or suffered under the affected Act or part; or\
	(c)	affect any right, privilege, obligation or liability acquired, accrued or incurred under the affected Act or part; or\
	(d)	affect any penalty, forfeiture or punishment incurred in respect of any offence committed against the affected Act or part; or\
	(e)	affect any investigation, legal proceeding or remedy in respect of any such right, privilege, obligation, liability, penalty, forfeiture or punishment.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 Any such investigation, legal proceeding or remedy may be instituted, continued or enforced, and any such penalty, forfeiture or punishment may be imposed, as if the affected Act or part had not been repealed or amended.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1985\fi-851\ri1933\sb122\partightenfactor0

\fs18 \cf0 Note:	The Act that makes the repeal or amendment, or provides for the instrument to make the repeal or amendment, may be different from, or the same as, the affected Act or the Act containing the part repealed or amended.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f2\i\fs22 \cf0 Interpretation\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\i0 \cf0 	(3)	A reference in subsection\'a0(1) or (2) to the repeal or amendment of an Act or of a part of an Act includes a reference to:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	a repeal or amendment effected by implication; and\
	(b)	the expiry, lapsing or cessation of effect of the Act or part; and\
	(c)	the abrogation or limitation of the effect of the Act or part; and\
	(d)	the exclusion of the application of the Act or part to any person, subject\uc0\u8209 matter or circumstance.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(4)	A reference in this section to a part of an Act includes a reference to any provision of, or words, figures, drawings or symbols in, an Act.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 10  References to amended or re\uc0\u8209 enacted Acts\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf0 		Where an Act contains a reference to a short title that is or was provided by law for the citation of another Act as originally enacted, or of another Act as amended, then:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	the reference shall be construed as a reference to that other Act as originally enacted and as amended from time to time; and\
	(b)	where that other Act has been repealed and re\uc0\u8209 enacted, with or without modifications, the reference shall be construed as including a reference to the re\u8209 enacted Act as originally enacted and as amended from time to time; and\
	(c)	if a provision of the other Act is repealed and re\uc0\u8209 enacted (including where the other Act is repealed and re\u8209 enacted), with or without modifications, a reference to the repealed provision extends to any corresponding re\u8209 enacted provision (whether or not the re\u8209 enacted provision has the same number as the repealed provision).\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 10A  References to amended or re\uc0\u8209 enacted laws of States and Territories\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf0 		Where an Act contains a reference to a short title or other citation that is or was provided by the law of a State or Territory for the citation of a law of that State or Territory as originally enacted or made, or as amended, then:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	the reference shall be construed as a reference to that law as originally enacted or made and as amended from time to time; and\
	(b)	where that law has been repealed and re\uc0\u8209 enacted or re\u8209 made, with or without modifications, the reference shall be construed as including a reference to the re\u8209 enacted or re\u8209 made law as originally enacted or made and as amended from time to time; and\
	(c)	if a provision of that law is repealed and re\uc0\u8209 enacted or re\u8209 made (including where that law is repealed and re\u8209 enacted or re\u8209 made), with or without modifications, a reference to the repealed provision extends to any corresponding re\u8209 enacted or re\u8209 made provision (whether or not the re\u8209 enacted or re\u8209 made provision has the same number as the repealed provision).\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 11\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
  Acts may be altered etc. in same session\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 		An Act may be altered, amended or repealed in the same session of Parliament in which it was passed.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 11A\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
  \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Inserting definitions into provisions or inserting items into lists or tables\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f2\i\b0\fs22 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Inserting definitions\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\i0 \cf0 	(1)	If an amending Act inserts a definition in a provision of the Act being amended, but does not specify the position in that provision where it is to be inserted, it is to be inserted in the appropriate alphabetical position, determined on a letter\uc0\u8209 by\u8209 letter basis.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f2\i \cf0 Inserting items into lists or tables\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\i0 \cf0 	(2)	If:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	an amending Act inserts an item into a list or table in a provision of the Act being amended, but does not specify the position in the list or table where the item is to be inserted; and\
	(b)	immediately before the insertion, the list or table was arranged alphabetically;\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 the item is inserted in the appropriate alphabetical position, determined on a letter\uc0\u8209 by\u8209 letter basis.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 11B\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
  Amending Act to be construed with amended Act\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 	(1)	Every Act amending another Act must be construed with the other Act as part of the other Act.\
	(2)	If:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	an Act (the 
\f3\i\b amending Act
\f1\i0\b0 ) amends another Act (the 
\f3\i\b principal Act
\f1\i0\b0 ); and\
	(b)	a provision (the 
\f3\i\b non\uc0\u8209 amending provision
\f1\i0\b0 ) of the amending Act does not amend the principal Act, but relates to an amendment of the principal Act made by another provision of the amending Act; and\
	(c)	a term is used in the non\uc0\u8209 amending provision that has a particular meaning in the principal Act or in a provision of the principal Act amended or included by the amending Act;\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 then the term has that meaning in the non\uc0\u8209 amending provision.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1985\fi-851\ri1933\sb122\partightenfactor0

\fs18 \cf0 Note:	Subsection\'a0(2) covers, for example, application, transitional and saving items in a Schedule to an amending Act that relate to amendments of a principal Act made by other items in the Schedule.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\fs22 \cf0 	(3)	Subsection\'a0(2) does not limit subsection\'a0(1).\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 Part\'a05\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\'97\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 General interpretation rules\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri1933\sl-160\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs16 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0   \
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 12  Every section a substantive enactment\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf0 		Every section of an Act shall have effect as a substantive enactment without introductory words.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 13  Material that is part of an Act\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf0 	(1)	All material from and including the first section of an Act to the end of:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	if there are no Schedules to the Act\'97the last section of the Act; or\
	(b)	if there are one or more Schedules to the Act\'97the last Schedule to the Act;\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 is part of the Act.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(2)	The following are also part of an Act:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	the long title of the Act;\
	(b)	any Preamble to the Act;\
	(c)	the enacting words for the Act;\
	(d)	any heading to a Chapter, Part, Division or Subdivision appearing before the first section of the Act.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(3)	However, text is not part of an Act, or a compilation of an Act within the meaning of the 
\f2\i Legislation Act 2003
\f1\i0 , if the text:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	only indicates the effect of an element of the Act; and\
	(b)	is accessible in an electronic version of the Act or compilation; and\
	(c)	does not appear in the printed text of the Act (or any amendment of the Act) as enacted by the Parliament, or any other printed version of the Act or compilation.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1985\fi-851\ri1933\sb122\partightenfactor0

\fs18 \cf0 Note:	This text is known as alternative text or \'93alt text\'94. Alternative text may be accessible in an electronic version of an Act or compilation that is published on an approved website under the 
\f2\i Legislation Act 2003
\f1\i0 . This text may, for example, aurally indicate the effect of a graphic image in an Act to assist users of the website who have visual disabilities.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 15A  Construction of Acts to be subject to Constitution\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf0 		Every Act shall be read and construed subject to the Constitution, and so as not to exceed the legislative power of the Commonwealth, to the intent that where any enactment thereof would, but for this section, have been construed as being in excess of that power, it shall nevertheless be a valid enactment to the extent to which it is not in excess of that power.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 15AA\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
  Interpretation best achieving Act\'92s purpose or object\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 		In interpreting a provision of an Act, the interpretation that would best achieve the purpose or object of the Act (whether or not that purpose or object is expressly stated in the Act) is to be preferred to each other interpretation.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 15AB  Use of extrinsic material in the interpretation of an Act\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf0 	(1)	Subject to subsection\'a0(3), in the interpretation of a provision of an Act, if any material not forming part of the Act is capable of assisting in the ascertainment of the meaning of the provision, consideration may be given to that material:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	to confirm that the meaning of the provision is the ordinary meaning conveyed by the text of the provision taking into account its context in the Act and the purpose or object underlying the Act; or\
	(b)	to determine the meaning of the provision when:\
\pard\tqr\tx1985\pardeftab720\li2098\fi-2098\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(i)	the provision is ambiguous or obscure; or\
	(ii)	the ordinary meaning conveyed by the text of the provision taking into account its context in the Act and the purpose or object underlying the Act leads to a result that is manifestly absurd or is unreasonable.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(2)	Without limiting the generality of subsection\'a0(1), the material that may be considered in accordance with that subsection in the interpretation of a provision of an Act includes:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	all matters not forming part of the Act that are set out in the document containing the text of the Act as printed by the Government Printer;\
	(b)	any relevant report of a Royal Commission, Law Reform Commission, committee of inquiry or other similar body that was laid before either House of the Parliament before the time when the provision was enacted;\
	(c)	any relevant report of a committee of the Parliament or of either House of the Parliament that was made to the Parliament or that House of the Parliament before the time when the provision was enacted;\
	(d)	any treaty or other international agreement that is referred to in the Act;\
	(e)	any explanatory memorandum relating to the Bill containing the provision, or any other relevant document, that was laid before, or furnished to the members of, either House of the Parliament by a Minister before the time when the provision was enacted;\
	(f)	the speech made to a House of the Parliament by a Minister on the occasion of the moving by that Minister of a motion that the Bill containing the provision be read a second time in that House;\
	(g)	any document (whether or not a document to which a preceding paragraph applies) that is declared by the Act to be a relevant document for the purposes of this section; and\
	(h)	any relevant material in the Journals of the Senate, in the Votes and Proceedings of the House of Representatives or in any official record of debates in the Parliament or either House of the Parliament.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(3)	In determining whether consideration should be given to any material in accordance with subsection\'a0(1), or in considering the weight to be given to any such material, regard shall be had, in addition to any other relevant matters, to:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	the desirability of persons being able to rely on the ordinary meaning conveyed by the text of the provision taking into account its context in the Act and the purpose or object underlying the Act; and\
	(b)	the need to avoid prolonging legal or other proceedings without compensating advantage.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 15AC  Changes to style not to affect meaning\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf0 		Where:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	an Act has expressed an idea in a particular form of words; and\
	(b)	a later Act appears to have expressed the same idea in a different form of words for the purpose of using a clearer style;\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 the ideas shall not be taken to be different merely because different forms of words were used.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 15AD\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
  Examples\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 		If an Act includes an example of the operation of a provision:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	the example is not exhaustive; and\
	(b)	the example may extend the operation of the provision.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 15B  Application of Acts in coastal sea\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f2\i\b0\fs22 \cf0 Coastal sea of Australia\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\i0 \cf0 	(1)	An Act is taken to have effect in, and in relation to, the coastal sea of Australia as if that coastal sea were part of Australia.\
	(2)	A reference in an Act to Australia, or to the Commonwealth, is taken to include a reference to the coastal sea of Australia.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f2\i \cf0 Coastal sea of external Territory\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\i0 \cf0 	(3)	An Act that is in force in an external Territory is taken to have effect in, and in relation to, the coastal sea of the Territory as if that coastal sea were part of the Territory.\
	(3A)	A reference in an Act to all or any of the external Territories (whether or not one or more particular Territories are referred to) is taken to include a reference to the coastal sea of any Territory to which the reference relates.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f2\i \cf0 Definition\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\i0 \cf0 	(4)	In this section, 
\f3\i\b coastal sea
\f1\i0\b0 :\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	in relation to Australia, means:\
\pard\tqr\tx1985\pardeftab720\li2098\fi-2098\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(i)	the territorial sea of Australia; and\
	(ii)	the sea on the landward side of the territorial sea of Australia and not within the limits of a State or internal Territory;\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 		and includes the airspace over, and the sea\uc0\u8209 bed and subsoil beneath, any such sea; and\
	(b)	in relation to an external Territory, means:\
\pard\tqr\tx1985\pardeftab720\li2098\fi-2098\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(i)	the territorial sea adjacent to the Territory; and\
	(ii)	the sea on the landward side of the territorial sea adjacent to the Territory and not within the limits of the Territory;\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 		and includes the airspace over, and the sea\uc0\u8209 bed and subsoil beneath, any such sea.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 15C  Jurisdiction of courts\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf0 		Where a provision of an Act, whether expressly or by implication, authorises a civil or criminal proceeding to be instituted in a particular court in relation to a matter:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	that provision shall be deemed to vest that court with jurisdiction in that matter;\
	(b)	the jurisdiction so vested is not limited by any limits to which any other jurisdiction of the court may be subject; and\
	(c)	in the case of a court of a Territory, that provision shall be construed as providing that the jurisdiction is vested so far only as the Constitution permits.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 16  References to the Sovereign\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf0 		In any Act references to the Sovereign reigning at the time of the passing of such Act, or to the Crown, shall be construed as references to the Sovereign for the time being.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 16A  References to the Governor\uc0\u8209 General\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf0 		Where, in an Act, the Governor\uc0\u8209 General is referred to, the reference shall be deemed to include:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	the person for the time being administering the Government of the Commonwealth; or\
	(b)	where the reference occurs in or in relation to a provision conferring on the Governor\uc0\u8209 General a power or function which the Governor\u8209 General or the person administering the Government of the Commonwealth has for the time being assigned to a person as his or her deputy, that last\u8209 mentioned person in his or her capacity as deputy;\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 and shall be read as referring to the Governor\uc0\u8209 General, or a person so deemed to be included in the reference, acting with the advice of the Executive Council.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 16B  References to the Governor of a State\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf0 		Where, in an Act, the Governor of a State is referred to, the reference shall be deemed to include the Governor for the time being of the State or any other person who is, for the time being, the chief executive officer or administrator of the government of the State.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 16BA  References to judge\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf0 		In any Act, a reference (whether general or otherwise) to a judge does not include a reference to a Judge, or an acting Judge, of the Local Court of the Northern Territory.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 16C  References to Stipendiary Magistrate and Magistrate\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf0 	(1)	Where, in an Act, reference is made to a Stipendiary Magistrate, the reference shall be read as including a reference to any Magistrate in respect of whose office an annual salary is payable.\
	(2)	Where, in an Act passed after the date of commencement of this section, reference is made to a Magistrate, the reference shall be read as a reference to:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	a Chief, Police, Stipendiary, Resident or Special Magistrate; or\
	(b)	any other Magistrate in respect of whose office an annual salary is payable.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(3)	In any Act, a reference to a Stipendiary Magistrate or Magistrate includes a reference to a Judge, or an acting Judge, of the Local Court of the Northern Territory.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 17A  Paper or document purporting to be printed by Government Printer\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf0 		For the purposes of an Act in which reference is made to a paper or document purporting to be printed by the Government Printer, the words \'93Government Printer of the Commonwealth\'94, \'93Government Printer of the Commonwealth of Australia\'94, \'93Commonwealth Government Printer\'94 or \'93Government Printer of Australia\'94 appearing on a paper or document shall be deemed to refer to the Government Printer.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 18A  Parts of speech and grammatical forms\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf0 		In any Act where a word or phrase is given a particular meaning, other parts of speech and grammatical forms of that word or phrase have corresponding meanings.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 18B  Titles of Chairs and Deputy Chairs\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f2\i\b0\fs22 \cf0 Chair titles\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\i0 \cf0 	(1)	For the purposes of this section, each of the following is a 
\f3\i\b chair title
\f1\i0\b0 :\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	Chair;\
	(b)	Chairperson;\
	(c)	Chairman;\
	(d)	Chairwoman.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(2)	A person occupying an office that is established by an Act and that has a chair title may choose to be referred to by:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	that chair title; or\
	(b)	another chair title; or\
	(c)	any other similar title.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(3)	If a person occupying an office that is established by an Act and that has a chair title does not choose to be referred to by a title mentioned in subsection\'a0(2), the person may be referred to by the chair title that someone addressing the person considers appropriate.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f2\i \cf0 Deputy chair titles\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\i0 \cf0 	(4)	For the purposes of this section, each of the following is a 
\f3\i\b deputy chair title
\f1\i0\b0 :\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	Deputy Chair;\
	(b)	Deputy Chairperson;\
	(c)	Deputy Chairman;\
	(d)	Deputy Chairwoman.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(5)	A person occupying an office that is established by an Act and that has a deputy chair title may choose to be referred to by:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	that deputy chair title; or\
	(b)	another deputy chair title; or\
	(c)	any other similar title.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(6)	If a person occupying an office that is established by an Act and that has a deputy chair title does not choose to be referred to by a title mentioned in subsection\'a0(5), the person may be referred to by the deputy chair title that someone addressing the person considers appropriate.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

