\cf0 refers to a Minister by describing a matter for which the Minister is responsible (for example, \'93the Minister responsible for the environment\'94)\cell 
\pard\intbl\itap1\pardeftab720\ri1933\sl240\sb60\partightenfactor0
\cf0 the Minister, or any of the Ministers, administering the Department of State of the Commonwealth that deals with the relevant matter on the relevant day.\cell \lastrow\row
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\fs22 \cf0 	(2)	Instruments including the following, as in force on the relevant day, or any earlier day, may be used to work out which Minister (or Ministers) is referred to under subsection\'a0(1):\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	an Administrative Arrangements Order;\
	(b)	a substituted reference order under section\'a019B.\
