\cf0 	(a)	an Administrative Arrangements Order;\
	(b)	a substituted reference order under section\'a019B.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li2353\fi-709\ri1933\sl-198\sb122\partightenfactor0

\fs18 \cf0 Note:	Substituted reference orders under section\'a019B may have effect in relation to days before the orders are made.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 19B  Machinery of government\'97substituted reference orders\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f2\i\b0\fs22 \cf0 Scope\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\i0 \cf0 	(1)	This section applies if:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	a provision of an Act refers to an authority (see subsection\'a0(7)); and\
	(b)	any of the following happens:\
\pard\tqr\tx1985\pardeftab720\li2098\fi-2098\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(i)	the authority is abolished;\
	(ii)	the name or title of the authority is changed;\
	(iii)	there is a change in the matters dealt with by the authority because of the effect of an Administrative Arrangements Order;\
	(iv)	the reference to the authority becomes no longer appropriate for any other reason.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f2\i \cf0 Substituted reference orders\'97Ministers, Departments, Agencies and offices\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\i0 \cf0 	(2)	The Governor\uc0\u8209 General may make a substituted reference order directing that the provision is to have effect for all purposes, on and after a day specified in the order:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	as if there were substituted, for the reference to the authority mentioned in subsection\'a0(1), a reference to another specified authority (or authorities); or\
	(b)	as if, in so far as the provision applies in a particular respect specified in the order, there were substituted, for the reference to the authority mentioned in subsection\'a0(1), a reference to another specified authority (or authorities).\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1985\fi-851\ri1933\sb122\partightenfactor0

\fs18 \cf0 Note 1:	For when the Governor\uc0\u8209 General may make a substituted reference order that relates to certain provisions of the 
\f2\i Australian Security Intelligence Organisation Act 1979
\f1\i0 , or the 
\f2\i Telecommunications (Interception and Access) Act 1979
\f1\i0 , that refer to the Attorney\uc0\u8209 General, see sections\'a05B and 6V of those Acts respectively.\
Note 2:	A substituted reference order may be amended or revoked in the same way as it is made (see subsection\'a033(3) of this Act).\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\fs22 \cf0 	(3)	The day specified in the order (as the day on and after which the order is to have effect) may be a day before the order is made.\
	(4)	A substituted reference order has effect according to its terms.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1985\fi-851\ri1933\sb122\partightenfactor0

\fs18 \cf0 Note:	The order has effect for the purpose of the making of any subsequent order under this section.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\fs22 \cf0 	(5)	A substituted reference order is a legislative instrument.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f2\i \cf0 Authority abolished and another established with the same name\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\i0 \cf0 	(6)	A substituted reference order must not be made only because an authority is abolished, and, immediately after its abolition, another authority of the same type, with the same name, is established.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1985\fi-851\ri1933\sb122\partightenfactor0

\fs18 \cf0 Note:	However, a substituted reference order may be made if either of the following happens in relation to the authority:\
\pard\pardeftab720\li2354\fi-369\ri1933\sl-198\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 (a)	there is a change in the matters dealt with by the authority because of the effect of an Administrative Arrangements Order (see subparagraph\'a0(1)(b)(iii));\
(b)	a reference to the authority becomes no longer appropriate for any other reason (see subparagraph\'a0(1)(b)(iv)).\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f2\i\fs22 \cf0 Definition of 
\f3\b authority\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\i0\b0 \cf0 	(7)	In this section:\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f3\i\b \cf0 authority
\f1\i0\b0  means any of the following:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	a Minister;\
	(b)	a Department of State of the Commonwealth;\
	(c)	any other Agency within the meaning of the 
\f2\i Public Service Act 1999
\f1\i0 ;\
	(d)	an office (including an APS employee\'92s office and any other appointment or position), or the holder of an office.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1985\fi-851\ri1933\sb122\partightenfactor0

\fs18 \cf0 Note:	Offices are offices in and for the Commonwealth (see section\'a021). An example is the office of Secretary of a Department of State.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

