\cf0 (a) exercising the powers, or performing the functions, of the relevant authority on the relevant day; or\
(b) determined under subsection\'a0(4).\cell \lastrow\row
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\fs22 \cf0 	(3)	The following instruments, as in force on the relevant day, or any earlier day, may be used to work out which authority is taken to be referred to under subsection\'a0(2):\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	an Administrative Arrangements Order;\
	(b)	a substituted reference order under section\'a019B.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li2353\fi-709\ri1933\sl-198\sb122\partightenfactor0

\fs18 \cf0 Note:	Substituted reference orders under section\'a019B may have effect in relation to days before the orders are made.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\fs22 \cf0 	(4)	The Minister administering the Department of State of the Commonwealth that deals with the relevant matter may, by notifiable instrument, make a determination for the purposes of item\'a03 of the table in subsection\'a0(2).\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1985\fi-851\ri1933\sb122\partightenfactor0

\fs18 \cf0 Note 1:	A determination may be amended or revoked in the same way as it is made (see subsection\'a033(3)).\
Note 2:	Notifiable instruments must be registered under the 
\f2\i Legislation Act 2003
\f1\i0 , but they are not subject to parliamentary scrutiny or sunsetting under that Act.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\fs22 \cf0 	(5)	To avoid doubt, if, because of this section, a provision of an agreement entered into by or on behalf of the Commonwealth is taken to require anything to be done by or in relation to any one of 2 or more Ministers, the provision is not taken to require it to be done in any particular case by or in relation to more than one of those Ministers.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f2\i \cf0 Definition of 
\f3\b authority\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\i0\b0 \cf0 	(6)	In this section:\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f3\i\b \cf0 authority
\f1\i0\b0  means any of the following:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	a Minister;\
	(b)	a Department of State of the Commonwealth;\
	(c)	any other Agency within the meaning of the 
\f2\i Public Service Act 1999
\f1\i0 ;\
	(d)	an office (including an APS employee\'92s office and any other appointment or position), or the holder of an office.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1985\fi-851\ri1933\sb122\partightenfactor0

\fs18 \cf0 Note:	Offices are offices in and for the Commonwealth (see section\'a021). An example is the office of Secretary of a Department of State.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 19D  Machinery of government changes\'97saving the validity of acts done by authorities\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f2\i\b0\fs22 \cf0 Saving the validity of acts done by authorities\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\i0 \cf0 	(1)	Subject to section\'a019E, the purported exercise or performance of a power, function or duty by or on behalf of an authority (see subsection\'a0(5)) is not invalid merely because, following a machinery of government change, the power, function or duty:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	is conferred or imposed on another authority; or\
	(b)	is conferred or imposed on the same authority under another name or title; or\
	(c)	is no longer conferred or imposed on any authority.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(2)	Subsection\'a0(1) only applies if the authority acted on the basis of a reasonable, but mistaken, belief about the occurrence, timing or nature of the machinery of government change.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f2\i \cf0 Machinery of government change\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\i0 \cf0 	(3)	For the purposes of this section, a 
\f3\i\b machinery of government change 
\f1\i0\b0 occurs if any of the following applies in relation to an authority:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	the authority is abolished;\
	(b)	the name or title of the authority is changed;\
	(c)	there is a change in the matters dealt with by the authority because of the effect of an Administrative Arrangements Order;\
	(d)	the authority no longer exercises or performs the power, function or duty for any other reason.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f2\i \cf0 Powers, functions and duties\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\i0 \cf0 	(4)	This section applies in relation to a power, function or duty purportedly exercised or performed by or on behalf of an authority, whether before or after the machinery of government change, under any of the following:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	an Act or legislative instrument;\
	(b)	an agreement entered into by or on behalf of the Commonwealth;\
	(c)	any other authorisation under a law of the Commonwealth.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f2\i \cf0 Definition of 
\f3\b authority\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\i0\b0 \cf0 	(5)	In this section:\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f3\i\b \cf0 authority
\f1\i0\b0  means any of the following persons or bodies:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	a Minister;\
	(b)	a Department of State of the Commonwealth;\
	(c)	any other Agency within the meaning of the 
\f2\i Public Service Act 1999
\f1\i0 ;\
	(d)	an office (including an APS employee\'92s office and any other appointment or position), or the holder of an office.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1985\fi-851\ri1933\sb122\partightenfactor0

\fs18 \cf0 Note:	Offices are offices in and for the Commonwealth (see section\'a021). An example is the office of Secretary of a Department of State.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 19E  Validity of acts done by Ministers\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf0 		If a Minister purports to exercise a power or perform a function or duty that is conferred or imposed on another Minister by an Act, the exercise of that power or the performance of that function or duty is not invalid merely because the power, function or duty is conferred or imposed on the other Minister.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 20  References to holders of appointments, offices and positions in Acts and Commonwealth agreements\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf0 		In a provision of an Act, or of an agreement entered into by or on behalf of the Commonwealth, a reference in general terms to the holder or occupier of an office, appointment or position includes all persons who for the time being:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	hold or occupy the office, appointment or position; or\
	(b)	perform the duties of the office, appointment or position.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 21  Office etc. means office etc. of the Commonwealth\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf0 	(1)	In any Act:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	references to any officer or office shall be construed as references to such officer or office in and for the Commonwealth; and\
	(b)	references to localities jurisdictions and other matters and things shall be construed as references to such localities jurisdictions and other matters and things in and of the Commonwealth.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(2)	In this section:\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f3\i\b \cf0 office
\f1\i0\b0  includes a position occupied by an APS employee.\

\f3\i\b officer
\f1\i0\b0  includes an APS employee.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 23  Rules as to gender and number\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf0 		In any Act:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	words importing a gender include every other gender; and\
	(b)	words in the singular number include the plural and words in the plural number include the singular.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 25A  Production of records kept in computers etc.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf0 		Where a person who keeps a record of information by means of a mechanical, electronic or other device is required by or under an Act to produce the information or a document containing the information to, or make a document containing the information available for inspection by, a court, tribunal or person, then, unless the court, tribunal or person otherwise directs, the requirement shall be deemed to oblige the person to produce or make available for inspection, as the case may be, a writing that reproduces the information in a form capable of being understood by the court, tribunal or person, and the production of such a writing to the court, tribunal or person constitutes compliance with the requirement.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 25B  Alterations of names and constitutions\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf0 	(1)	Where an Act alters the name of a body (whether or not the body is incorporated) or alters the name of an office, then:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	the body or office continues in existence under the new name so that its identity is not affected; and\
	(b)	in any Act, in any instrument under an Act, in any award or other industrial determination or order or any industrial agreement, in any other order (whether executive, judicial or otherwise), in any contract, in any pleading in, or process issued in connection with, any legal or other proceedings or in any other instrument, a reference to the body or the office under the former name shall, except in relation to matters that occurred before the alteration took place, be construed as a reference to the body or the office under the new name.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(1A)	Where a law of a State or Territory alters the name of a body (whether or not incorporated) or of an office, then a reference in an Act or an instrument made under an Act to the body or office under the former name is to be construed, except in relation to matters that occurred before the alteration, as a reference to the body or office under the new name.\
	(2)	Where an Act alters the constitution of a body (whether or not the body is incorporated), then:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	the body continues in existence as newly constituted so that its identity is not affected;\
	(b)	the alteration does not affect any functions, powers, property, rights, liabilities or obligations of the body;\
	(c)	the alteration does not affect any legal or other proceedings instituted or to be instituted by or against the body, and any legal or other proceedings that might have been continued or commenced by or against the body as previously constituted may be continued or commenced by or against the body as newly constituted; and\
	(d)	the alteration does not affect any investigation or inquiry being or proposed to be undertaken by any tribunal, authority or person into any action taken or practice engaged in by the body before the alteration took place, and any investigation or inquiry that might have been continued or commenced into any such action or practice may be continued or commenced as if the action had been taken or the practice had been engaged in by the body as newly constituted.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(3)	In this section:\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f3\i\b \cf0 office
\f1\i0\b0  includes a position occupied by an APS employee.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 25C  Compliance with forms\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf0 		Where an Act prescribes a form, then strict compliance with the form is not required and substantial compliance is sufficient.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 25D  Content of statements of reasons for decisions\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf0 		Where an Act requires a tribunal, body or person making a decision to give written reasons for the decision, whether the expression \'93reasons\'94, \'93grounds\'94 or any other expression is used, the instrument giving the reasons shall also set out the findings on material questions of fact and refer to the evidence or other material on which those findings were based.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 Part\'a06\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\'97\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Service of documents\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri1933\sl-160\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs16 \cf0   \
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 28A  Service of documents\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf0 	(1)	For the purposes of any Act that requires or permits a document to be served on a person, whether the expression \'93serve\'94, \'93give\'94 or \'93send\'94 or any other expression is used, then the document may be served:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	on a natural person:\
\pard\tqr\tx1985\pardeftab720\li2098\fi-2098\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(i)	by delivering it to the person personally; or\
	(ii)	by leaving it at, or by sending it by pre\uc0\u8209 paid post to, the address of the place of residence or business of the person last known to the person serving the document; or\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(b)	on a body corporate\'97by leaving it at, or sending it by pre\uc0\u8209 paid post to, the head office, a registered office or a principal office of the body corporate.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1985\fi-851\ri1933\sb122\partightenfactor0

\fs18 \cf0 Note:	The 
\f2\i Electronic Transactions Act 1999
\f1\i0  deals with giving information in writing by means of an electronic communication.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\fs22 \cf0 	(2)	Nothing in subsection\'a0(1):\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	affects the operation of any other law of the Commonwealth, or any law of a State or Territory, that authorises the service of a document otherwise than as provided in that subsection; or\
	(b)	affects the power of a court to authorise service of a document otherwise than as provided in that subsection.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 29  Meaning of service by post\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf0 	(1)	Where an Act authorises or requires any document to be served by post, whether the expression \'93serve\'94 or the expression \'93give\'94 or \'93send\'94 or any other expression is used, then the service shall be deemed to be effected by properly addressing, prepaying and posting the document as a letter and, unless the contrary is proved, to have been effected at the time at which the letter would be delivered in the ordinary course of post.\
	(2)	This section does not affect the operation of section\'a0160 of the\'a0
\f2\i Evidence Act 1995
\f1\i0 .\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 Part\'a07\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\'97\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 Powers, functions and duties\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri1933\sl-160\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs16 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0   \
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 33  Exercise of powers and performance of functions or duties\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f2\i\b0\fs22 \cf0 Powers, functions and duties may be exercised or must be performed as the occasion requires\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\i0 \cf0 	(1)	Where an Act confers a power or function or imposes a duty, then the power may be exercised and the function or duty must be performed from time to time as occasion requires.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f2\i \cf0 Meaning of 
\f3\b may\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\i0\b0 \cf0 	(2A)	Where an Act assented to after the commencement of this subsection provides that a person, court or body may do a particular act or thing, and the word \'93may\'94 is used, the act or thing may be done at the discretion of the person, court or body.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f2\i \cf0 Powers, functions and duties of bodies not affected by membership vacancies\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\i0 \cf0 	(2B)	Where an Act confers a power or function, or imposes a duty, on a body, whether incorporated or unincorporated, the exercise of the power or the performance of the function or duty is not affected merely because of a vacancy or vacancies in the membership of the body.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f2\i \cf0 Power to make instrument includes power to vary or revoke etc. instrument\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\i0 \cf0 	(3)	Where an Act confers a power to make, grant or issue any instrument of a legislative or administrative character (including rules, regulations or by\uc0\u8209 laws) the power shall be construed as including a power exercisable in the like manner and subject to the like conditions (if any) to repeal, rescind, revoke, amend, or vary any such instrument.\
	(3AA)	If a condition (the 
\f3\i\b ongoing condition
\f1\i0\b0 ):\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	must be satisfied before the making, granting or issuing of an instrument; and\
	(b)	is capable of ceasing to be satisfied after the making, granting or issuing of the instrument;\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 subsection\'a0(3) has effect, in relation to the repeal, rescission or revocation of the instrument, as if the reference to like conditions (to the extent that the reference relates to the ongoing condition) were a reference to the ongoing condition ceasing to be satisfied.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1985\fi-851\ri1933\sb122\partightenfactor0

\fs18 \cf0 Example:	A Minister may give a person a written permission if, among other things, the Minister is satisfied the person is of good character.\
	This condition is capable of ceasing to be satisfied after the giving of the permission.\
	The Minister may repeal, rescind or revoke the permission in the like manner if the Minister ceases to be satisfied that the person is of good character.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f2\i\fs22 \cf0 Scope of powers in respect of matters\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\i0 \cf0 	(3A)	Where an Act confers a power to make, grant or issue any instrument of a legislative or administrative character (including rules, regulations or by\uc0\u8209 laws) with respect to particular matters (however the matters are described), the power shall be construed as including a power to make, grant or issue such an instrument with respect to some only of those matters or with respect to a particular class or particular classes of those matters and to make different provision with respect to different matters or different classes of matters.\
	(3AB)	If an Act confers on a person or authority the power to make an instrument (except a legislative instrument, a notifiable instrument or a rule of court):\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	specifying, declaring or prescribing a matter; or\
	(b)	doing anything in relation to a matter;\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 then, in exercising the power, the person or authority may identify the matter by reference to a class or classes of matters.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1985\fi-851\ri1933\sb122\partightenfactor0

\fs18 \cf0 Note:	This provision has a parallel, in relation to legislative instruments, and notifiable instruments, in section\'a013 of the 
\f2\i Legislation Act 2003
\f1\i0 .\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\fs22 \cf0 	(3AC)	For the purposes of subsections\'a0(3A) and (3AB), 
\f3\i\b matter 
\f1\i0\b0 includes thing, person and animal.\
	(3B)	Where an Act confers a power to make, grant or issue any instrument of a legislative or administrative character (including rules, regulations or by\uc0\u8209 laws), the power shall not be taken, by implication, not to include the power to make provision for or in relation to a particular aspect of a matter by reason only that provision is made by the Act in relation to another aspect of that matter or in relation to another matter.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f2\i \cf0 Power to make appointment to an office or place\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\i0 \cf0 	(4)	Where an Act confers upon any person or authority a power to make appointments to any office or place, the power shall be construed as including a power to appoint a person to act in the office or place until:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	a person is appointed to the office or place; or\
	(b)	the expiration of 12 months after the office or place was created or became vacant, as the case requires;\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 whichever first happens, and as also including a power to remove or suspend any person appointed, and to appoint another person temporarily in the place of any person so suspended or in place of any sick or absent holder of such office or place.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 		Provided that where the power of such person or authority to make any such appointment is only exercisable upon the recommendation or subject to the approval or consent of some other person or authority, such power to make an appointment to act in an office or place or such power of removal shall only be exercisable upon the recommendation or subject to the approval or consent of such other person or authority.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f2\i \cf0 Power to make instrument prescribing penalties\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\i0 \cf0 	(5)	Where an Act confers a power to make, grant or issue an instrument (including rules, regulations or by\uc0\u8209 laws) prescribing penalties not exceeding a specified amount or imprisonment for a specified period, that limitation on the penalties that may be prescribed does not prevent the instrument from requiring the making of a statutory declaration.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 33AA  Power to appoint includes power to reappoint\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf0 		If an Act confers on a person or body a power to make an appointment, the power is taken to include a power of reappointment.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 33AB  Validity of things done under appointments under Acts\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf0 		Anything done by or in relation to a person purporting to act under an appointment (including an acting appointment) under an Act is not invalid merely because:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	for any appointment\'97the occasion for the appointment had not arisen; or\
	(b)	for any appointment\'97there was a defect or irregularity in connection with the appointment; or\
	(c)	for any appointment\'97the appointment had ceased to have effect; or\
	(d)	for an acting appointment\'97the occasion to act had not arisen or had ceased.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 33A  Acting in offices or positions\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f2\i\b0\fs22 \cf0 Acting appointments\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\i0 \cf0 	(1)	Where a provision of an Act (other than subsection\'a033(4) of this Act) confers on a person or body (in this section called the 
\f3\i\b appointer
\f1\i0\b0 ) a power to appoint a person (in this section called the 
\f3\i\b appointee
\f1\i0\b0 ) to act in a particular office, then, except so far as the Act otherwise provides, the following paragraphs apply in relation to an appointment made under the provision:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	the appointment may be expressed to have effect only in the circumstances specified in the instrument of appointment;\
	(b)	the appointer may:\
\pard\tqr\tx1985\pardeftab720\li2098\fi-2098\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(i)	determine the terms and conditions of the appointment, including remuneration and allowances; and\
	(ii)	terminate the appointment at any time;\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(ba)	where the appointment is to act in a vacant office, the appointee must not continue to act in the office for more than 12 months;\
	(c)	where the appointee is acting in an office other than a vacant office and the office becomes vacant while the appointee is acting, then, subject to paragraph\'a0(a), the appointee may continue so to act until:\
\pard\tqr\tx1985\pardeftab720\li2098\fi-2098\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(i)	the appointer otherwise directs;\
	(ii)	the vacancy is filled; or\
	(iii)	a period of 12 months from the day of the vacancy ends;\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 		whichever happens first;\
	(d)	the appointment ceases to have effect if the appointee resigns in writing delivered to the appointer;\
	(e)	while the appointee is acting in the office:\
\pard\tqr\tx1985\pardeftab720\li2098\fi-2098\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(i)	the appointee has and may exercise all the powers, and shall perform all the functions and duties, of the holder of the office; and\
	(ii)	that or any other Act applies in relation to the appointee as if the appointee were the holder of the office.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f2\i \cf0 Acting by operation of law\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\i0 \cf0 	(2)	If a provision of an Act provides for a person to act in a particular office (without the need for an appointment), then, except so far as the Act otherwise provides, while the person is acting in the office:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	the person has and may exercise all the powers, and must perform all the functions and duties, of the holder of the office; and\
	(b)	the Act or any other Act applies in relation to the person as if the person were the holder of the office.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(3)	Anything done by or in relation to a person purporting to act in the office mentioned in subsection\'a0(2) is not invalid merely because the occasion to act had not arisen or had ceased.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f2\i \cf0 Definition\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\i0 \cf0 	(4)	In this section:\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f3\i\b \cf0 office
\f1\i0\b0  includes a position occupied by an APS employee.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 33B  Participation in meetings by telephone etc.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf0 	(1)	This section applies to a body (whether or not incorporated) established by an Act if the Act requires or permits meetings of the members of the body to be held.\
	(2)	The body may permit its members to participate in a meeting, or all meetings, by:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	telephone; or\
	(b)	closed\uc0\u8209 circuit television; or\
	(c)	any other means of communication.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(3)	A member who participates in a meeting under a permission under subsection\'a0(2) is taken to be present at the meeting and to form part of any quorum for the meeting.\
	(4)	The members of a body participating in a meeting for which a permission under subsection\'a0(2) is in effect may all participate by a means of communication referred to in that subsection.\
	(5)	A meeting for which a permission under subsection\'a0(2) is in effect may be held at 2 or more places at the same time.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 34  Power to hear and determine a matter includes power to receive evidence and examine witnesses etc.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf0 		Any court, Judge, justice of the peace, officer, commissioner, arbitrator, or other person authorised by law, or by consent of parties, to hear and determine any matter, shall have authority to receive evidence and examine witnesses and to administer an oath or affirmation to all witnesses legally called before them respectively.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 34AAA  Exercise of powers etc. by holders etc. of offices or positions\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf0 		If an Act confers a power or function or imposes a duty on a person holding or occupying an office or position as such, then the power may be exercised or the function or duty must be performed by the person for the time being holding or occupying the office or position.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 34AAB\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
  Minister may authorise others to perform functions or duties or exercise powers on his or her behalf\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 	(1)	A Minister (the 
\f3\i\b authorising Minister
\f1\i0\b0 ) who administers (whether alone or jointly with one or more other Ministers) an Act or a provision of an Act may authorise:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	a Minister who does not administer the Act or provision; or\
	(b)	a member of the Executive Council who is not a Minister;\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 to act on behalf of the authorising Minister in the performance of functions or duties, or the exercise of powers, that the authorising Minister may perform or exercise under the Act or provision.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(2)	An authorisation under subsection\'a0(1) in relation to an Act or a provision of an Act extends to the performance of functions or duties, or the exercise of powers, that the authorising Minister may perform or exercise under an instrument (including a regulation, rule or Proclamation) having effect under or for the purposes of the Act or provision.\
	(3)	Subject to subsection\'a0(4), an authorisation under subsection\'a0(1) may be expressed:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	to have effect only during a period or periods, or during the existence of a circumstance or circumstances, referred to in the authorisation; or\
	(b)	to take effect immediately, or at a time referred to in the authorisation, and afterwards to continue to have effect until another person is appointed to the office held by the authorising Minister.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(4)	An authorisation under subsection\'a0(1) may be revoked at any time by the authorising Minister.\
	(5)	An authorisation under subsection\'a0(1), and the revocation of such an authorisation, must be in writing.\
	(6)	This section does not affect the giving, under a power existing apart from this section, of an authorisation to a Minister or other member of the Executive Council to act on behalf of another Minister.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 34AA  Delegation to persons holding, occupying or performing the duties of an office or position\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf0 		Where an Act confers power to delegate a function, duty or power, then the power of delegation shall not be construed as being limited to delegating the function, duty or power to a specified person but shall be construed as including a power to delegate the function, duty or power to any person from time to time holding, occupying, or performing the duties of, a specified office or position, even if the office or position does not come into existence until after the delegation is given.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 34AB  Effect of delegation\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f2\i\b0\fs22 \cf0 General\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\i0 \cf0 	(1)	Where an Act confers power on a person or body (in this section called the 
\f3\i\b authority
\f1\i0\b0 ) to delegate a function, duty or power:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	the delegation may be made either generally or as otherwise provided by the instrument of delegation;\
	(b)	the powers that may be delegated do not include that power to delegate;\
	(c)	a function, duty or power so delegated, when performed or exercised by the delegate, shall, for the purposes of the Act, be deemed to have been performed or exercised by the authority;\
	(d)	a delegation by the authority does not prevent the performance or exercise of a function, duty or power by the authority; and\
	(e)	if the authority is not a person, section\'a034A applies as if it were.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f2\i \cf0 Addition of functions, duties or powers\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\i0 \cf0 	(2)	If:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	a person (the 
\f3\i\b delegator
\f1\i0\b0 ) or body (also the 
\f3\i\b delegator
\f1\i0\b0 ) delegates all the person\'92s or body\'92s functions, duties or powers under an Act, or a provision of an Act, to another person or body; and\
	(b)	the Act is amended to give the delegator one or more additional functions, duties or powers under the Act or provision; and\
	(c)	the delegation is in force immediately before the amendment takes effect;\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 then, on and after the amendment taking effect, the delegation is taken to include the additional functions, duties or powers.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb240\partightenfactor0

\f2\i \cf0 Alteration of functions, duties or powers\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\i0 \cf0 	(3)	If:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	a person or body delegates one or more of the person\'92s or body\'92s functions, duties or powers under an Act, or a provision of an Act, to another person or body; and\
	(b)	the Act is amended to alter the scope of one or more of those functions, duties or powers under the Act or provision; and\
	(c)	the delegation is in force immediately before the amendment takes effect;\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 then, on and after the amendment taking effect, the delegation is taken to include the functions, duties or powers as altered.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 34A\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
  Exercise of powers and performance of functions or duties that depend upon the \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 opinion etc. of \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
delegates\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 		If:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	under an Act, a person\'92s exercise of a power, or a person\'92s performance of a function or duty, is dependent upon the person\'92s opinion, belief or state of mind in relation to a matter; and\
	(b)	that power, function or duty has been delegated under that or any other Act;\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 the delegate may exercise that power, or may perform that function or duty, upon the delegate\'92s opinion, belief or state of mind in relation to that matter.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 34B  Presentation of papers to the Parliament\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf0 	(1)	Where, by an Act or a law of a Territory, provision is made requiring or permitting the presentation (however expressed) of a paper to the Parliament or to both Houses, or to each or either House, of the Parliament, it is sufficient compliance with the provision, in relation to a House, if:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	the paper is presented in that House in accordance with the rules or orders of the House or, if, under the rules or orders of the House, papers are deemed to be presented to the House if they are delivered to the Clerk of the House and recorded in the records of the proceedings of the House, the paper is so delivered and recorded;\
	(b)	where the provision provides for a specified person to present the paper or to cause the paper to be presented\'97that person, or any other person who could by virtue of this Act or of any other Act, or of a law of a Territory, act in the place of that person, makes or causes to be made, as the case may be, the presentation or the delivery of the paper referred to in the last preceding paragraph; and\
	(c)	where the provision specifies a period within which the paper is to be presented\'97the presentation, or the delivery and recording, of the paper referred to in paragraph\'a0(a) takes place within that period.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(1A)	For the purposes of an Act or a law of a Territory that refers to papers presented (however the presentation is described) to the Parliament or to both Houses, or to each or either House, of the Parliament:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0

\f4 \cf0 	(\uc0\u1072 )	presentation of a paper in a House of the Parliament in accordance with the rules or orders of the House; or
\f1 \
	(b)	if, under the rules or orders of a House of the Parliament, papers are to be deemed to be presented to the House if they are delivered to the Clerk of the House and recorded in the records of the proceedings of the House\'97such a delivery and recording of a paper;\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 shall be deemed to have been presentation of the paper to that House, as described in that Act or law, effected or caused by the person who so presented or delivered the paper or caused the paper to be so presented or delivered.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(2)	In this section, 
\f3\i\b paper
\f1\i0\b0  includes:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	an ordinance, rule, regulation or by\uc0\u8209 law;\
	(b)	a report; and\
	(c)	any other document or instrument whatsoever.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 34C  Periodic reports\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf0 	(1)	In this section:\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f3\i\b \cf0 periodic report
\f1\i0\b0  means a regular report relating to:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	the activities, operations, business or affairs of a person; or\
	(b)	the administration, operation or working of an Act or part of an Act;\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 during a particular period that ends on or after 30\'a0June 1983.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f3\i\b \cf0 person 
\f1\i0\b0 includes a body corporate, office, commission, authority, committee, tribunal, board, institute, organization or other body however described.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(2)	Where an Act requires a person to furnish a periodic report to a Minister but does not specify a period within which the report is to be so furnished, that person shall furnish the report to the Minister as soon as practicable after the end of the particular period to which the report relates and, in any event, within 6 months after the end of that particular period.\
	(3)	Where an Act requires a person to furnish a periodic report to a Minister for presentation to the Parliament but does not specify a period within which the report is to be so presented, that Minister shall cause a copy of the periodic report to be laid before each House of the Parliament within 15 sitting days of that House after the day on which he or she receives the report.\
	(4)	Where this or any other Act requires a person to furnish a periodic report to a Minister within a specified period and that person is of the opinion that it will not be reasonably possible to comply with the requirement, that person may, within the specified period, apply to the Minister for an extension of the period, and, where he or she does so apply, he or she shall furnish to the Minister a statement in writing explaining why, in that person\'92s opinion, it will not be reasonably possible to comply with the requirement.\
	(5)	A Minister may, on application under subsection\'a0(4), grant such extension as he or she considers reasonable in the circumstances.\
	(6)	Notwithstanding subsection\'a0(2) and the provisions of any other Act, where a Minister grants an extension pursuant to an application under subsection\'a0(4):\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	the Minister shall cause to be laid before each House of the Parliament, within 3 sitting days of that House after the day on which he or she grants the extension, a copy of the statement furnished pursuant to subsection\'a0(4) in respect of the application together with a statement specifying the extension granted and his or her reasons for granting the extension;\
	(b)	the person who made the application shall furnish the periodic report to the Minister within the period as so extended; and\
	(c)	the Minister shall cause a copy of the periodic report to be laid before each House of the Parliament within 15 sitting days of that House after the day on which he or she receives the report.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(7)	Where this or any other Act requires a person to furnish a periodic report to a Minister within a specified period or an extension of that period under this section and that person fails to do so:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	that person shall, not later than 14 days after the end of that specified period or extension, as the case may be, furnish to the Minister a statement in writing explaining why the report was not furnished as required; and\
	(b)	the Minister shall cause a copy of the statement to be laid before each House of the Parliament within 3 sitting days of that House after the day on which he or she receives the statement.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(7A)	This section applies to the Australian Security Intelligence Organisation, the Australian Signals Directorate and the Office of National Intelligence in the following way:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	subsection\'a0(3) does not apply;\
	(b)	if an extension is granted under subsection\'a0(5), then for the purpose of subsection\'a0(6), paragraph\'a0(6)(c) is to be disregarded.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(8)	This section does not apply in relation to the Australian Secret Intelligence Service.\
