\fs18 \cf0 Example 1:	If a claim may be made between 1\'a0September and 30\'a0November, a claim may be made on both 1\'a0September and 30\'a0November.\
Example 2:	If a permission begins on the first day of a financial year, the permission is in force on that day.\
Example 3:	If a licence continues until 31\'a0March, the licence is valid up to and including 31\'a0March.\
Example 4:	If a person\'92s right to make submissions ends on the last day of a financial year, the person may make submissions on that day.\
Example 5:	If a variation of an agreement is expressed to operate from 30\'a0June, the variation starts to operate on 1\'a0July.\
Example 6:	If a decision is made on 2\'a0August and a person has 28 days after the day the decision is made to seek a review of the decision, the 28\uc0\u8209 day period begins on 3\'a0August.\
Example 7:	If a person must give a notice to another person at any time during the period of 7 days before the day a proceeding starts and the proceeding starts on 8\'a0May, the notice may be given at any time during the 7\uc0\u8209 day period starting on 1\'a0May and ending on 7\'a0May.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\fs22 \cf0 	(2)	If:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	an Act requires or allows a thing to be done; and\
	(b)	the last day for doing the thing is a Saturday, a Sunday or a holiday;\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 then the thing may be done on the next day that is not a Saturday, a Sunday or a holiday.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1985\fi-851\ri1933\sb122\partightenfactor0

\fs18 \cf0 Example:	If a person has until 31\'a0March to make an application and 31\'a0March is a Saturday, the application may be made on Monday 2\'a0April.\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\fs22 \cf0 	(3)	In this section:\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f3\i\b \cf0 holiday
\f1\i0\b0 , in relation to the time for doing a thing, means:\
\pard\tqr\tx1531\pardeftab720\li1644\fi-1644\ri1933\sb40\partightenfactor0
\cf0 	(a)	a day that is a public holiday in the place in which the thing is to be or may be done; and\
	(b)	if the thing is to be or may be done at a particular office or other place\'97a day on which the place or office is closed for the whole day.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 37  Expressions of time\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf0 		Where in an Act any reference to time occurs, such time shall, unless it is otherwise specifically stated, be deemed in each State or part of the Commonwealth to mean the legal time in that State or part of the Commonwealth.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 37A\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
  Attainment of particular age\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 		For the purposes of any Act, the time at which a person attains a particular age expressed in years is the commencement of the relevant anniversary of the date of the birth of that person.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

