\f0\b\fs24 \cf0 47  Construction of resolutions\
\pard\tqr\tx1021\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb180\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs22 \cf0 		Where any resolution is or has been passed by either House of the Parliament in purported pursuance of any Act, then the resolution shall be read and construed subject to the Constitution and to the Act under which it purports to have been passed, to the intent that where the resolution would, but for this section, have been construed as being in excess of authority, it shall nevertheless be a valid resolution to the extent to which it is not in excess of authority.\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1134\fi-1134\ri1933\sb280\partightenfactor0

